<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-15-0153 </DOCNO><TEXT>The problem of the critical (quench or recovery) delay times between twoconsecutive heat pulses acting upon cooled composite superconductor isnumerically investigated. The dependence of critical delay times on thepulse energies, separation distance between pulses, and transport currentvalues is determined. It is shown that the two pulses-technique may giveimportant information on the dynamical stability of superconducting magnets.</TEXT></DOC>